---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'January 1, 2025';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service | Skyhooked on Comfort"
  description="Terms of service for Skyhooked on Comfort HVAC services in Phoenix, AZ."
>
  <section class="bg-charcoal-50 py-16 border-b border-neutral-200">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h1 class="font-display font-extrabold text-charcoal text-3xl sm:text-4xl mb-2">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="font-body text-neutral-500 text-sm">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white py-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 prose prose-neutral max-w-none">
      <div class="space-y-10 font-body text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-charcoal text-xl mb-3">1. Agreement to Terms</h2>
          <p>By scheduling service, using our website, or engaging Skyhooked on Comfort ("Company," "we," "us") for any HVAC services in the Phoenix Valley, you agree to these Terms of Service. If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use our services or website.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-charcoal text-xl mb-3">2. Services Provided</h2>
          <p>Skyhooked on Comfort provides residential and commercial HVAC installation, repair, maintenance, and related services in the greater Phoenix, Arizona metropolitan area. All services are provided by licensed Arizona contractors (ROC #312489).</p>
          <p class="mt-3">Service scope, pricing, and terms for specific jobs are set forth in written estimates or service agreements provided before work begins. These Terms of Service supplement, but do not replace, the terms in those specific agreements.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-charcoal text-xl mb-3">3. Estimates and Pricing</h2>
          <p>Written estimates are valid for 30 days from the date issued unless otherwise stated. Estimates are based on information available at the time of assessment; if additional issues are discovered during service, we will communicate them and obtain your approval before proceeding with additional work.</p>
          <p class="mt-3">We provide flat-rate pricing on standard residential repairs and installations. Pricing for complex commercial projects and systems requiring diagnosis will be quoted based on time and materials or a fixed-price contract, as agreed in writing before work begins.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-charcoal text-xl mb-3">4. Payment Terms</h2>
          <p>Residential service: payment is due upon completion of service. We accept major credit cards, debit cards, check, and cash. Financing options are available through our third-party financing partners; financing approval is subject to the terms and conditions of those partners.</p>
          <p class="mt-3">Commercial accounts: payment is due within 30 days of invoice unless otherwise agreed in a commercial service agreement. Accounts more than 30 days past due are subject to a 1.5% monthly late charge and may be referred to collections.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-charcoal text-xl mb-3">5. Cancellation and Rescheduling</h2>
          <p>We ask for at least 24 hours' notice to cancel or reschedule a service appointment. Appointments cancelled with less than 2 hours' notice, or for which we arrive and cannot access the property, may be subject to a trip charge of up to $75.</p>
          <p class="mt-3">Emergency service calls are subject to the emergency rates disclosed at the time of scheduling. Emergency rate disclosure is provided before dispatch.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-charcoal text-xl mb-3">6. Warranties</h2>
          <p><strong>Labor warranty:</strong> We warrant our labor for 1 year from the date of service on standard residential repairs and installations. If a repair we performed fails within the warranty period due to defects in our workmanship, we will re-perform the repair at no charge.</p>
          <p class="mt-3"><strong>Equipment warranty:</strong> New equipment is covered by the manufacturer's warranty, which varies by brand and product. We assist with warranty registration and provide service records that satisfy most manufacturers' warranty maintenance documentation requirements. Specific warranty terms are those of the equipment manufacturer.</p>
          <p class="mt-3">Warranties do not cover damage from misuse, failure to maintain, acts of nature, pre-existing conditions not identified in the original service assessment, or modifications made by other parties after our service.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-charcoal text-xl mb-3">7. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p>To the maximum extent permitted by Arizona law, our total liability to you for any claim arising from our services shall not exceed the amount you paid us for the specific service giving rise to the claim.</p>
          <p class="mt-3">We are not liable for indirect, incidental, consequential, or punitive damages, including lost profits, business interruption, food spoilage, or similar damages, even if we have been advised of the possibility of such damages.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-charcoal text-xl mb-3">8. Access and Site Conditions</h2>
          <p>You agree to provide safe and reasonable access to the equipment and areas necessary for us to perform the agreed services. If site conditions (hazardous materials, structural issues, unsafe access) prevent us from completing work safely, we reserve the right to stop work and discuss alternative approaches.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-charcoal text-xl mb-3">9. Governing Law</h2>
          <p>These terms are governed by the laws of the State of Arizona. Any disputes shall be resolved in the courts of Maricopa County, Arizona.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-charcoal text-xl mb-3">10. Contact</h2>
          <p>Questions about these terms? Contact us at:</p>
          <div class="bg-charcoal-50 rounded-xl p-5 mt-3 border border-neutral-200">
            <p class="font-display font-semibold text-charcoal">Skyhooked on Comfort</p>
            <p>Phoenix, AZ</p>
            <p>Phone: <a href="tel:4801234567" class="text-sky hover:underline">(480) 123-4567</a></p>
            <p>Arizona ROC #312489</p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
